dcterms:description: A dataset consisting of approximately 8 minutes of video of a closed environment where five Zebra finches (Taeniopygia guttata) are kept. The video has 14,459 frames, with a resolution of 4,096 × 2,048 pixels. The birds appear small in the images, measuring about 10 × 20 pixels, and can fly at speeds of up to 20 pixels per frame.
dcterms:title: NUBird2022
